-- Iraq to Ship 15 Basrah Light Cargoes in Second Half of January
-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 2012-01-13T16:35:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-13/iraq-to-ship-15-basrah-light-cargoes-in-second-half-of-january.html
Iraq will ship 15 cargoes of  Basrah
Light (ZOSPBLAS)  crude oil for loading in the second half of January from
the  Persian Gulf , according to a loading program obtained by
Bloomberg News.  A total of 25.715 million barrels, or 1.61 million barrels
a day, will be loaded from Basrah Oil Terminal, the plan showed.
The program comprises 11 cargoes of 2 million barrels each,
three shipments of 1 million barrels and one 715,000-barrel lot.  Basrah Light has a density of 30.2 degrees on the American
Petroleum Institute scale and a sulfur content of 2.92 percent,
according to BP Plc.  Loading programs are schedules of crude shipments compiled
by field operators to allow buyers and sellers to plan their
supply and trading activities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sherry Su in London at 
